# Copy to `.env` (never commit `.env`).
#
# Quick start (from repo root):
#   cp .env.example .env
#   pnpm install && (cd web && pnpm install)
#   pnpm dev:server          # API only → http://127.0.0.1:18410
#   pnpm dev                 # API + Flow UI dev → :18410 + http://127.0.0.1:3333/app/
#   pnpm smoke               # offline verification (no server required)
#
# Docker:
#   pnpm docker:up:server     # backend only (no Flow UI container)
#   pnpm docker:up            # backend + Flow UI (default compose)
#   pnpm docker:up:ui-only    # static Flow UI only (set VITE_API_ORIGIN at build)
#
# **Non-secret settings:** edit `config/agent_platform.yaml` (URLs, DB path, planner flags, etc.).
# **Secrets:** set only here or in the process environment — never commit real keys.
#
# Precedence: shell environment > `.env` > `config/agent_platform.yaml` > code defaults.
#
# Optional: point to another YAML file
# AGENT_PLATFORM_CONFIG_YAML=/path/to/agent_platform.yaml
#
# --- Lean server ---
# Backend ships with `/config` (LLM proxy settings) and `/ui` (process demo).
# Optional Flow UI lives in web/ — baked into unified `agent-platform` image.
# Run modes (one container): backend (default) | ui | all
# AGENT_PLATFORM_CONTAINER_MODE=backend
#
# Backend + Flow UI (two containers):
#   pnpm docker:up
#
# Backend only:
#   pnpm docker:up:server
#
# Cross-origin browser access when Flow UI is on another host/port:
# CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://127.0.0.1:18408
#
# For a single-container run with embedded LLM proxy, see `docker-compose.agent-only.yml`:
#   - AGENT_PLATFORM_DB_PATH, AGENT_PLATFORM_WORKSPACE_ROOT, CONFIG_DIR, CONFIG_PATH
#   - LLM_ORCHESTRATOR_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18410/v1 (same process as the API)
# External microservices call the HTTP API with the master key; see `/api-guide` and
# `scripts/external_microservice_example.py`.

# --- secrets (keep in `.env` only) ---
AGENT_PLATFORM_MASTER_KEY=

# Optional cloud / API keys (embedded LLM proxy)
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# AIMLAPI_API_KEY=
# AIMLAPI_OPENAI_BASE=https://api.aimlapi.com/v1
# Claude (Anthropic OpenAI-compatible surface). Models are pulled live from /v1/models.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_OPENAI_BASE=https://api.anthropic.com/v1
# ANTHROPIC_VERSION=2023-06-01
# LM_STUDIO_API_KEY=

# BYOK (bring-your-own-key): clients send X-BYOK-Provider + X-BYOK-Api-Key headers
# (optional X-BYOK-Base-Url) to forward through their own key, spending no platform
# quota. Custom base URLs are allowed only for a provider's canonical host; add more
# hosts (comma-separated) to permit proxied/regional endpoints. No key config needed.
# BYOK_ALLOWED_HOSTS=gateway.example.com,proxy.internal.example.com

# Image generation backend (separate from chat providers; OpenAI /v1/images/generations shape).
# Point at a local diffusion service (e.g. ComfyUI/diffusers) to enable POST /v1/images/generations.
# Unset => image_generation capability is unconfigured and returns a structured 501.
# IMAGE_API_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:9000
# IMAGE_DEFAULT_MODEL=flux.1-schnell

# Optional: require `Authorization: Bearer` on `/api/v1/*` (config UI auth bar or web env as VITE_AGENT_PLATFORM_MASTER_KEY)
# VITE_AGENT_PLATFORM_MASTER_KEY=

# Workspace-scoped token for an external microservice (mint via /tokens or POST /workspaces/{id}/api-tokens/)
# AGENT_PLATFORM_TOKEN=agp_...

# Resume stranded processes on server startup (default: enabled). Set 0 to disable.
# AGENT_PLATFORM_RESUME_ON_STARTUP=1

# Docker: rewrite 127.0.0.1 → host.docker.internal for LM_STUDIO_API_BASE / OLLAMA_API_BASE (default on in container).
# AGENT_PLATFORM_LOCAL_LLM_DOCKER_FIX=0

# --- performance tuning (optional) ---
# Uvicorn workers: docker-compose defaults to 1. With SQLite (default DB), compose clamps to 1 worker even if you set >1.
# AGENT_PLATFORM_UVICORN_WORKERS=8
# AGENT_PLATFORM_UVICORN_KEEPALIVE_SECONDS=30
#
# DAG scheduler concurrency for dependency-ready tasks. Keep below provider/API bottlenecks.
# AGENT_PLATFORM_DAG_MAX_CONCURRENT_TASKS=12
#
# Thread pools for Python/native libraries inside the container.
# UV_THREADPOOL_SIZE=16
# OMP_NUM_THREADS=16
# OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS=16
# MKL_NUM_THREADS=16
# NUMEXPR_NUM_THREADS=16
#
# Multi-agent LLM concurrency (web UI agents calling POST /api/v1/chat at once).
# Raise AGENT_PLATFORM_CHAT_MAX_CONCURRENT if your upstream (Ollama/AIML API/etc.)
# can sustain more; excess agent calls queue rather than failing outright. Upstream
# rate-limit responses (HTTP 429/503, or a body naming "too many concurrent requests")
# also auto-retry with backoff — tune via the two retry vars below.
# AGENT_PLATFORM_CHAT_MAX_CONCURRENT=8
# ORCHESTRATOR_HTTP_RATE_LIMIT_MAX_RETRIES=6
# ORCHESTRATOR_HTTP_RATE_LIMIT_BACKOFF_MS=400
